data.name: Label3.Text
data.value: 1. The index is plotted here along with the chart pattern indicator. The indicator is the blue line near the bottom of the chart. Red vertical lines are bearish, green bars are bullish and white is neutral. Do NOT use this indicator to trade because signals can appear or disappear for up to seven days. Use the indicator as background information only.

data.name: Label1.Text
data.value: 2. Enter the start and end dates for the period you wish to chart (From and To text boxes). Select the type of chart you wish to view (signal changes, all signals, or indicator only). Enter one symbol for an index (Index text box). The index is not included in the CPI calculation. The Browse button can help find the index file. Click Help for this form. Click Stop to halt a calculation and Start to begin one. The Done button returns you to the prior form. Clipboard copies CPI information (after a run completes) to the clipboard for pasting into another program. Results shows a week's worth of numerical results.

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value: This form will calculate and display the chart pattern indicator. For best results, select a large number of stocks (I use 600) on the Main Form. Use DAILY price data (that is, not intraday data). Make sure your files cover the date range.
